    var buoyHistoryInfo = @"
<ul>
<li>Ultimate origin of buoys is unknown.</li>
<li>1295: Seaman's manual refers to navigation buoys in the Guadalquivir River, Spain.</li>
<li>Early medieval mentions of buoys in the French / Belgian River Maas.</li>
<li>1358: Record of a barrel buoy in the Dutch Maasmond (Maas Sluis / Maasgat).</li>
<li>Early buoys:
<ul>
<li>Likely timber beams or rafts</li>
<li>Barrel buoy was difficult to secure to seabed</li>
</ul>
